title: For Sale:  French MLE 1907/15 Berthier Lebel Rifle 8mm Lebel RESTORED
postcontent:
This rifle has been a display piece in my home for over 30 years. I bought it in the early 1980's from a retired neighbor who's full time  hobby and passion was restoring old military firearms. Especially those from WWI & WWII. 

It's a French MLE 1907/15 rifle chambered in the 8mm Lebel round. 

The care and attention to detail used in restoring was fantastic and this rifle looks absolutely beautiful. 

Finish on metal and wood are near perfect.

The wood appears to have been done in hand rubbed oil that's likely similar to it's original finish. It's not a high gloss finish but rather more of a deep sheen. I'm not 100% sure what was used on the metal, but its a low gloss deep black that really looks quite nice. 

Everything functions mechanically and the bore is in nice shape without any rust, pitting or corrosion. 

I have never shot this rifle although I feel that you could. That said you must always have a firearm this old inspected by a competent gunsmith before shooting it. Rifle was made in 1927 so it's 87 years old. 

Rifle comes with leather sling, original Lebel brass handle needle bayonet and 4 clips of original 8mm French Lebel ammo that came with the rifle. 

All in all its a darn fine specimen of a firearm that's just not much seen anymore. 

Asking $500 local sale only with pickup in the Brandon area. I'm not going to ship this rifle so please don't ask. Buyer must be a Florida resident at least 18 years old.

Thanks for looking.

This sale is for S&W 4506-1

S&W 3rd Gen 4506-1. One of the final full size 5" Stainless Steel 45's S&W made before switching to the Polymer guns. Most think this is by far the best generation of S&W 45's, with the 4506-1 specifically being possibly the best version of any full size S&W semi-auto pistols, having proven reliability and accuracy. 

Seems a few of the 4506-1's were built with tighter tolerances for even better accuracy, and are known as 4506-1 "R4". Based on info from S&W forum, the one offered for sale here seems to look like one of these "special" versions: Has the larger barrel hood, roll marks on the slide and frame, "VA" serial prefixes, fixed Novak sights, and the roll marks on the frame were two lines - serial number and "MOD 4506-1".

Comes with two 8 round factory magazines, and Hogue grips installed, as well as original grips. Operates in either Single action or Double action (SA/DA). Ambidextrous safety and decocker lever.

$700 firm, FTF West Central Florida (might travel a little ways), must be over 21, and legally allowed to own a firearm.

Finances forces me to thin the herd. Have two S&W 3rd Gen 45's and cannot determine which one to keep, so both are offered, with you deciding. Both are capable of sub 2" groups at 25 yards. Do I keep the famous 4506-1 model that most LEO's wish they still had, and that Detective Sonny Crockett used in Miami Vice, as well as current TV Detective Vic Mackey uses in the Shield?
